                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18211205-103-victim1178 t18211205-103-viclabel644"></join> to Mr. Collins. On the 14th of November, I was walking in <placeName id="t18211205-103-crimeloc645">Glasshouse-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18211205-103-crimeloc645" type="placeName" value="Glasshouse-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18211205-103-crimeloc645" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18211205-103-off642 t18211205-103-crimeloc645"></join>. Griffiths came up and asked if I had lost any thing; I felt, and missed my handkerchief, which he produced.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18211205-103-person1180">
                  JOHN 
                  GRIFFITHS
               <interp inst="t18211205-103-person1180" type="surname" value="GRIFFITHS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-103-person1180" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-103-person1180" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I belong to the Humane Society. I saw the prosecutor walking along; the prisoner and two others were together, one of them took the handkerchief out of the prosecutor's pocket, and gave it to the prisoner. I went and told him to follow me, and I pursued and took the prisoner; and as he ran he took the handkerchief out of his hat, and threw it down an area, it lodged on the rails, I picked it up and secured him.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I never saw it.</p>
